Package civitas.celestis.math.vector

Interface Vector

All Superinterfaces:
Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
MutableVector, Quaternion, RichColor, Vector2, Vector3, Vector4, Vector5, Vertex
public interface Vector extends Serializable

A multidimensional number which has a direction and magnitude. This interface defines the contract of a vector.

Vectors can not only be used for spacial data, but can be used for any application which require the collective use of multiple scalars as one object. First-party examples include representing colors using a four-dimensional vector. (RGBA)

In order to ensure flawless arithmetic operation between vectors or other numbers, the non-finite constraint is enforced in all vectors. Non-finite values (e.g. Double.NaN, Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY, Double.NEGATIVE_INFINITY) will trigger an exception in the constructor.
